1
00:02:02,589 --> 00:02:04,614
Quiet, please.

2
00:02:29,649 --> 00:02:31,344
Excuse me.

3
00:02:37,390 --> 00:02:40,416
You know, if you haven't learned
your lines by now...

4
00:02:40,593 --> 00:02:42,151
...probably too late.

5
00:02:42,328 --> 00:02:44,228
Thanks. Real encouraging.

6
00:02:44,397 --> 00:02:46,262
Nice outfit.

7
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,425
- So you nervous?
- Yes.

8
00:02:51,638 --> 00:02:53,196
So where are you sitting?

9
00:02:53,373 --> 00:02:55,807
Front row, center balcony
with Alanna.

10
00:02:57,510 --> 00:02:59,410
Oh, I didn't know she was coming.

11
00:02:59,579 --> 00:03:01,809
Yeah, are you kidding?
We wouldn't miss it.

12
00:03:02,182 --> 00:03:05,151
Got your tickets, got your tickets,
got your programs.

13
00:03:05,318 --> 00:03:06,717
Programs, $5.

14
00:03:06,886 --> 00:03:08,581
- Hey, hey.
- Programs, $5.

15
00:03:08,755 --> 00:03:10,552
- Oh, hey, sweetie.
- Hey.

16
00:03:10,723 --> 00:03:12,918
- I'm sorry I'm late. I got your text.
- Yeah?

17
00:03:13,293 --> 00:03:16,353
I had to do a knee replacement.
Three hours. Can you fix this?

18
00:03:16,529 --> 00:03:18,861
They need to quit treating you
like a resident.

19
00:03:19,232 --> 00:03:21,826
- They think I am. Tickets?
- I don't. Thought you did.

20
00:03:22,302 --> 00:03:24,202
May I please see
your tickets, quick?

21
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:28,329
Let's check them out.
Make sure these babies are legit.

22
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:30,467
You're bronze package.

23
00:03:30,643 --> 00:03:33,203
- Problem?
- Minor.

24
00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:35,506
I can bump you guys up
to platinum package.

25
00:03:35,682 --> 00:03:38,913
It's a small fee, $22. Basically
better A/C in the building...

26
00:03:39,285 --> 00:03:42,686
...better seats and the proceeds
go to a charity, a really cool one.

27
00:03:42,855 --> 00:03:45,415
- You're Truman.
- Am I German?

28
00:03:45,592 --> 00:03:46,718
Daughter's in the play.

29
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:49,453
- Yes, I am Truman.
- She's told us all about you.

30
00:03:49,929 --> 00:03:52,659
All right, thanks for buying
the platinum package.

31
00:03:52,865 --> 00:03:54,765
Excuse me. Hey.

32
00:03:54,934 --> 00:03:56,925
- Hey, how are you?
- I'm good.

33
00:03:57,303 --> 00:04:00,898
- Did you get a program?
- No, I didn't. I'll just look off yours.

34
00:04:01,474 --> 00:04:03,271
So that took a while.

35
00:04:05,545 --> 00:04:07,706
Yeah. I went to see a friend.

36
00:04:11,351 --> 00:04:12,909
How is she?

37
00:04:15,288 --> 00:04:16,482
She's nervous.

38
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:20,786
Well, I guess I would be too.

39
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:22,928
Thank you for joining us tonight...

40
00:04:23,296 --> 00:04:25,230
- Excuse us.
- ...for our production.

41
00:04:25,798 --> 00:04:29,632
Special welcome to our alumni
and guests. Good to have you.

42
00:04:30,303 --> 00:04:32,362
We are proud
of our spring production...

43
00:04:32,538 --> 00:04:35,268
...one of our enduring traditions
at the university.

44
00:04:35,441 --> 00:04:38,501
But this year, we are featuring
some fresh new faces.

45
00:04:38,678 --> 00:04:41,704
So join me, as we welcome
to the stage our cast...

46
00:04:41,881 --> 00:04:47,285
...as they perform an original play
written by yours truly.

47
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,478
Thank you. Thank you.

48
00:04:49,656 --> 00:04:52,386
Thank you. Thank you.

49
00:04:53,726 --> 00:04:58,629
So without further ado,
I present to you Annabella.

50
00:05:26,826 --> 00:05:27,986
Annabella?

51
00:05:29,629 --> 00:05:32,792
- Is that you, Desmond?
- Hello, Annabella.

52
00:05:32,965 --> 00:05:35,763
You can dispense
with the pleasantries, Desmond.

53
00:05:35,935 --> 00:05:37,869
It's a bit trifle, don't you think?

54
00:05:38,037 --> 00:05:41,063
If you'd just let me explain,
I'm confident we would agree.

55
00:05:41,441 --> 00:05:46,777
You need to know that my family has,
well, certain standards for me.

56
00:05:46,946 --> 00:05:49,676
Standards in which I do not meet?

57
00:05:49,849 --> 00:05:53,012
Admit it, Desmond. Please.

58
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:03,824
- I've realized...
- I've...

59
00:06:03,996 --> 00:06:05,623
I've realized...

60
00:06:06,999 --> 00:06:09,968
...that I have certain standards
that you do not meet.

61
00:06:10,136 --> 00:06:12,536
- That's not right.
- I'll set sail on my own.

62
00:06:12,739 --> 00:06:16,368
It's time I discovered the life
I've always dreamed of...

63
00:06:16,542 --> 00:06:18,476
...but thought impossible.

64
00:06:30,089 --> 00:06:32,421
Get it together, Hannah.

65
00:06:34,827 --> 00:06:36,454
I'm leaving, Desmond.

66
00:06:37,029 --> 00:06:38,496
Leaving?

67
00:06:39,532 --> 00:06:41,625
Where, Annabella?

68
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:45,768
I'm...

69
00:06:46,639 --> 00:06:47,833
What?

70
00:06:50,643 --> 00:06:51,769
Hannah!

71
00:06:52,812 --> 00:06:54,143
Excuse me.

72
00:06:55,581 --> 00:06:56,809
Hannah.

73
00:06:57,917 --> 00:07:00,715
Hannah. Hannah.

74
00:07:11,998 --> 00:07:14,762
Get her inhaler. In the brown bag!
Get her inhaler!

75
00:07:14,967 --> 00:07:18,630
- We need Hannah's bag.
- Hannah. No, no, Hannah.

76
00:07:18,805 --> 00:07:21,535
No, listen to me. Hannah! Hannah!

77
00:07:32,819 --> 00:07:33,808
Hannah. No.

78
00:08:19,565 --> 00:08:22,762
Dr. Jacob Lawson, is he in surgery?

79
00:08:27,273 --> 00:08:28,240
Thanks.

80
00:08:41,821 --> 00:08:45,723
Yeah, but what I'd like to do
is maybe give her the tests.

81
00:08:45,892 --> 00:08:48,053
- Yeah.
- Just to make sure.

82
00:08:53,032 --> 00:08:54,863
Hi, sweetie.

83
00:08:55,735 --> 00:08:59,762
I was looking for you. They said you'd
be here. What was that about?

84
00:09:00,573 --> 00:09:01,904
Does he know what happened?

85
00:09:05,177 --> 00:09:06,144
No, no, no.

86
00:09:06,312 --> 00:09:09,679
The full test results
won't be in for another couple days.

87
00:09:09,849 --> 00:09:13,785
But your PTF levels were fine
when you stayed here overnight.

88
00:09:13,953 --> 00:09:17,855
So Dr. Stewart thinks
it's good for us all to go home.

89
00:09:18,658 --> 00:09:20,023
Is that not what you think?

90
00:09:21,127 --> 00:09:23,288
Yeah, no-- No, I do. I agree.

91
00:09:23,663 --> 00:09:27,895
I agree with Dr. Stewart. He's a
specialist. We need to do what he says.

92
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:31,161
All right, well,
I'm gonna go get changed, I guess.

93
00:09:31,337 --> 00:09:32,964
Okay.

94
00:10:13,980 --> 00:10:16,949
"lf you just let me explain,
I'm confident we would agree.

95
00:10:17,116 --> 00:10:22,053
You need to know that my family,
they have certain standards for me."

96
00:10:22,221 --> 00:10:24,587
Standards in which I do not meet?

97
00:10:25,257 --> 00:10:26,849
Admit it, Desmond, please.

98
00:10:27,026 --> 00:10:31,053
It's time I discovered the life I've always
dreamed of but thought impossible.

99
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:39,699
Predictions?

100
00:10:46,278 --> 00:10:48,803
Is there something
you're not telling me, Dad?

101
00:10:50,182 --> 00:10:53,174
I was thinking about
asking you the same thing.

102
00:10:55,221 --> 00:10:56,279
- Jacob.
- Hi.

103
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:57,987
Hey, Grace.

104
00:10:58,157 --> 00:11:00,682
- Hannah.
- Hi.

105
00:11:02,895 --> 00:11:05,363
It's good to see you all again.

106
00:11:05,731 --> 00:11:09,223
Although, I wish it was under
better circumstances.

107
00:11:12,371 --> 00:11:15,670
So how have you felt this week?
Any new symptoms or problems?

108
00:11:15,841 --> 00:11:19,208
No, I feel fine.

109
00:11:21,447 --> 00:11:25,383
Well, I've looked
at your EEG and MRI...

110
00:11:26,886 --> 00:11:29,116
...and it looks like
we need to reconsider...

111
00:11:29,288 --> 00:11:32,724
...our current management
of the epilepsy.

112
00:11:33,225 --> 00:11:39,095
Stress, sleep deprivation and alcohol
can increase your risk of seizures.

113
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:44,295
Since you haven't had a seizure since
childhood I just have to ask--

114
00:11:44,904 --> 00:11:46,735
I don't do drugs. I don't drink.

115
00:11:46,906 --> 00:11:49,204
I don't smoke, I don't...

116
00:11:50,142 --> 00:11:53,134
If that's what you mean.

117
00:11:55,181 --> 00:11:56,375
Oh, I see.

118
00:11:58,784 --> 00:12:02,686
BPD, acute asthma, seizures,
multiple hip surgeries.

119
00:12:04,790 --> 00:12:07,088
Most when you were too young
to remember.

120
00:12:07,259 --> 00:12:09,227
I remember some.

121
00:12:12,832 --> 00:12:16,131
Hannah, I believe that
everything you suffered from...

122
00:12:16,302 --> 00:12:18,293
...is related.

123
00:12:19,839 --> 00:12:21,272
Why am I sick?

124
00:12:25,344 --> 00:12:29,440
You were born very prematurely,
24 weeks.

125
00:12:30,983 --> 00:12:34,350
Premature birth
or low birth weight...

126
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:38,251
...and a traumatic delivery
can be associated with this condition.

127
00:12:39,125 --> 00:12:41,116
I was premature?

128
00:12:41,293 --> 00:12:43,227
And that's why I'm sick?

129
00:12:43,395 --> 00:12:46,296
Hannah,
we're concerned about you...

130
00:12:46,465 --> 00:12:50,799
...because of the physical and
emotional symptoms that you're having.

131
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:55,373
What do you mean "emotional"?

132
00:13:07,419 --> 00:13:09,410
Your father e-mailed me this.

133
00:13:18,564 --> 00:13:20,361
"l feel dead inside.

134
00:13:21,133 --> 00:13:23,533
No, something worse than death.

135
00:13:25,004 --> 00:13:26,062
I am still a child.

136
00:13:27,173 --> 00:13:30,870
A child trying to find a place
in this world.

137
00:13:31,043 --> 00:13:32,806
I have many unanswered questions.

138
00:13:32,978 --> 00:13:35,913
Questions I feel
but can't even begin to speak...

139
00:13:36,081 --> 00:13:38,345
...because there are no words
to express them.

140
00:13:40,019 --> 00:13:41,919
Something is missing.

141
00:13:42,087 --> 00:13:44,851
Why, God, do I feel...?

142
00:13:46,592 --> 00:13:48,890
Do I feel unwanted?

143
00:13:49,361 --> 00:13:51,352
Why do I feel I have
no right to exist?

144
00:13:51,530 --> 00:13:55,364
Why do I spend more time
wanting to end my life than live it?"

145
00:13:56,936 --> 00:13:59,928
You--? You read my journal?

146
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:06,242
Hannah, I believe
that what you're feeling is normal...

147
00:14:06,412 --> 00:14:08,004
...and is even expected.

148
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:10,171
What is--? What is this about?

149
00:14:13,085 --> 00:14:14,916
What? What?

150
00:14:18,123 --> 00:14:21,524
Hannah, we're not
your biological parents.

151
00:14:25,164 --> 00:14:28,565
Hang on.
That's not how I wanted to tell you.

152
00:14:30,469 --> 00:14:33,233
Why didn't you tell me
I was adopted?

153
00:14:39,511 --> 00:14:40,978
Okay.

154
00:14:42,615 --> 00:14:44,310
You were born premature...

155
00:14:44,483 --> 00:14:47,452
...because you were the survivor
of a failed abortion.

156
00:14:52,491 --> 00:14:56,621
Your physical, and, I believe,
your emotional symptoms...

157
00:14:56,996 --> 00:15:00,227
...can be traced to this
as they have in other cases.

158
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:03,926
I can only speak
to your physical symptoms...

159
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:07,861
...but I'm suggesting
that you begin treatment...

160
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:12,636
...for your psychological symptoms
as well, immediately.

161
00:15:13,012 --> 00:15:18,416
Now, I'm prescribing a new medication
to help control your seizures...

162
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:22,076
...and you have to continue
to take your current medication.

163
00:15:22,988 --> 00:15:26,583
- Hannah.
- No, I have to go.

164
00:15:26,992 --> 00:15:29,893
- Hey, I don't think that's a good idea.
- Don't touch me.

165
00:15:56,989 --> 00:15:58,388
Hello?

166
00:15:59,391 --> 00:16:01,120
- Hi.
- Hey, I can't hear you.

167
00:16:01,293 --> 00:16:03,557
I have set your iron on fire.

168
00:16:03,729 --> 00:16:05,026
Can I call you back?

169
00:16:07,066 --> 00:16:09,626
Jason, the iron's on fire.
It's in my hand.

170
00:16:10,002 --> 00:16:12,596
It's really loud in here.
Can I call you back?

171
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:14,030
The iron's on fire.

172
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:18,406
Sure, it's fine, whatever.
Call me back.

173
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:23,042
Bye.

174
00:16:44,470 --> 00:16:46,438
We didn't even talk about
the e-mail.

175
00:16:46,605 --> 00:16:48,334
What am I supposed to do?

176
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:51,965
My daughter is contemplating suicide,
I'm supposed to do nothing?

177
00:16:52,144 --> 00:16:54,374
- I don't think so.
- It's not like that.

178
00:16:54,546 --> 00:16:58,607
Hannah, sweetheart, please sit down.
We need to talk to you.

179
00:16:58,784 --> 00:17:01,617
You've had 19 years to talk to me.

180
00:17:01,787 --> 00:17:04,221
I can understand
why you'd feel that way...

181
00:17:04,390 --> 00:17:07,416
...but, please, I would like
to talk to you now. So sit.

182
00:17:07,593 --> 00:17:10,084
I don't wanna sit down.
I don't wanna talk.

183
00:17:10,262 --> 00:17:13,129
- What do you want?
- I wanna see my birth certificate.

184
00:17:13,298 --> 00:17:17,200
- Why?
- Because I wanna know who I am.

185
00:17:17,669 --> 00:17:19,398
This is who you are, Hannah.

186
00:17:19,571 --> 00:17:22,267
Okay, well, I wanna know
who my birth mother is.

187
00:17:22,441 --> 00:17:24,534
I wanna know how I can find her.

188
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:27,008
- I can't do that.
- Why?

189
00:17:27,179 --> 00:17:30,342
Because I can't. I can't...

190
00:17:32,184 --> 00:17:35,085
I can't because I have no idea
who your birth mother is.

191
00:17:35,254 --> 00:17:39,782
- I have no idea where she is. She--
- Here, it's your birth certificate.

192
00:17:41,794 --> 00:17:43,557
Thank you.

193
00:18:02,781 --> 00:18:04,339
Hel--

194
00:18:04,516 --> 00:18:06,381
Who's there?

195
00:18:07,453 --> 00:18:09,444
Hello?

196
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:12,280
It's me.

197
00:18:12,458 --> 00:18:15,586
- You can put down the pepper spray.
- Great.

198
00:18:18,130 --> 00:18:21,588
- How did you know I was here?
- You are way too predictable.

199
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:24,201
- I am not.
- I am not.

200
00:18:26,538 --> 00:18:30,133
- Can I come in?
- No, I'm mad at you.

201
00:18:38,283 --> 00:18:42,242
- What are you doing?
- I am taking off my shoes.

202
00:18:42,421 --> 00:18:47,552
- Why are you taking off your shoes?
- Because I'm sorry.

203
00:18:47,726 --> 00:18:50,251
And I don't like
when people are mad at me...

204
00:18:50,429 --> 00:18:52,294
...especially you.

205
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:57,131
So are you doing all right?

206
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:00,362
No.

207
00:19:01,607 --> 00:19:03,700
You wanna talk about it?

208
00:19:04,676 --> 00:19:06,200
No.

209
00:19:20,559 --> 00:19:22,686
My whole life is a lie.

210
00:19:24,530 --> 00:19:26,361
Why do you say that?

211
00:19:27,199 --> 00:19:28,689
The hip surgeries...

212
00:19:31,236 --> 00:19:32,567
...the nightmares...

213
00:19:32,738 --> 00:19:35,468
...the asthma...

214
00:19:35,874 --> 00:19:37,899
...the seizures...

215
00:19:39,444 --> 00:19:41,605
...all of it's connected.

216
00:19:43,682 --> 00:19:48,244
My parents aren't my parents.

217
00:19:50,489 --> 00:19:52,684
They adopted me.

218
00:20:00,899 --> 00:20:04,835
They adopted me because my
birth mother tried to abort me.

219
00:20:10,809 --> 00:20:12,868
I guess I wasn't supposed
to survive.

220
00:20:14,913 --> 00:20:17,245
And I barely did.

221
00:20:17,783 --> 00:20:22,311
All I know, or all they will let me know
is that I was born in a hospital...

222
00:20:22,487 --> 00:20:26,890
...in Mobile, Alabama,
which is 12 hours away.

223
00:20:27,759 --> 00:20:31,525
And I don't know
how I would get there.

224
00:20:32,898 --> 00:20:35,696
Or if I did go, what I would do.

225
00:20:37,803 --> 00:20:43,764
I just-- I want answers.
I want answers to all these questions.

226
00:20:44,476 --> 00:20:48,572
I wanna be able to get on with my life,
you know?

227
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:56,452
Because right now, I just feel stuck.

228
00:21:00,959 --> 00:21:04,292
Like there's--
Like there's no way out.

229
00:21:09,401 --> 00:21:12,495
I'm stuck in this place that I hate.

230
00:21:22,648 --> 00:21:25,242
I told you I didn't wanna
talk about it.

231
00:21:27,919 --> 00:21:32,322
Hannah, l-- I'm sorry.

232
00:21:34,893 --> 00:21:37,726
I don't know what else to say.

233
00:21:40,399 --> 00:21:45,564
I imagine things
are pretty terrible right now...

234
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:49,368
...but they'll get better.

235
00:21:51,910 --> 00:21:54,606
That's really optimistic.

236
00:21:58,450 --> 00:22:02,511
Look, things are gonna
work out, okay? I promise.

237
00:22:02,688 --> 00:22:04,622
You'll know what to do.

238
00:22:07,392 --> 00:22:09,917
What makes you so sure?

239
00:22:10,595 --> 00:22:12,495
I know you.

240
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:17,391
I don't even know me.

241
00:22:22,974 --> 00:22:27,070
- Who's that?
- Alanna. I'll just call her back.

242
00:22:27,446 --> 00:22:29,710
No, no, no. You can answer it.

243
00:22:29,881 --> 00:22:32,714
- Are you sure?
- Yeah, I mean, you should.

244
00:22:35,854 --> 00:22:37,481
Hello.

245
00:22:38,390 --> 00:22:39,755
Hey.

246
00:22:40,826 --> 00:22:44,728
No, no, just hanging out.
What's up?

247
00:22:46,932 --> 00:22:49,901
Yeah, yeah, sure,
I guess you can come.

248
00:22:50,068 --> 00:22:53,003
Look can l...?
Actually, can I call you back?

249
00:22:53,372 --> 00:22:54,930
Yeah. No, I promise.

250
00:22:55,741 --> 00:22:58,039
All right, thanks. See you.

