You know what the last thing...

739
01:05:36,399 --> 01:05:39,391
...was that I remember
before I blacked out?

740
01:05:41,137 --> 01:05:43,901
The last thing
that went through my mind?

741
01:05:45,675 --> 01:05:47,233
Falling.

742
01:05:49,545 --> 01:05:52,412
Falling into perfect blue water...

743
01:05:54,417 --> 01:05:56,408
...holding your hand.

744
01:05:58,621 --> 01:06:01,556
Why have you
always been there for me?

745
01:06:05,161 --> 01:06:06,594
Good night.

746
01:06:06,963 --> 01:06:08,260
Good night.

747
01:07:15,664 --> 01:07:17,131
Can I help you?

748
01:07:17,299 --> 01:07:19,233
I'm here to see Cindy Hastings.

749
01:07:19,402 --> 01:07:22,633
Oh, she's out at the moment.
Would you like to wait?

750
01:07:24,273 --> 01:07:27,640
Do you have a restroom I could use?
Thanks.

751
01:07:29,378 --> 01:07:32,677
Conwell and Hastings,
Attorney at Law. How may I help you?

752
01:07:33,549 --> 01:07:36,518
Yeah, she's really booked up
for the day, though.

753
01:07:37,153 --> 01:07:38,620
Monday?

754
01:08:29,271 --> 01:08:32,069
Hi, can I help you?

755
01:08:34,643 --> 01:08:39,307
I-- I'm sorry, Stacey didn't tell me
that I had another appointment.

756
01:08:39,482 --> 01:08:43,418
I'm sorry that I'm just, like,
in your office like this.

757
01:08:44,286 --> 01:08:47,483
I'm Hannah. I'm Hannah Lawson.

758
01:08:47,656 --> 01:08:49,715
Are you one of the new interns?

759
01:08:49,892 --> 01:08:53,692
You know, I would love to talk
but I have a lunch appointment.

760
01:08:54,697 --> 01:08:56,255
I was...

761
01:08:56,866 --> 01:09:02,168
I was born October the seventh, 1991...

762
01:09:02,671 --> 01:09:05,469
...at Mobile General Hospital.

763
01:09:08,911 --> 01:09:13,507
I guess I came here because I hoped
that that meant something to you.

764
01:09:29,398 --> 01:09:32,231
Stacey, could you
please cancel my lunch...

765
01:09:32,401 --> 01:09:34,460
...and hold all my calls.

766
01:09:40,442 --> 01:09:42,740
I don't know what you wanted.

767
01:09:44,813 --> 01:09:48,909
Hey, honey, you ready? We gotta go.
Lilly's waiting for us in the lobby.

768
01:09:49,285 --> 01:09:52,777
Oh, I'm sorry. Who's this?

769
01:09:53,656 --> 01:09:55,521
I...

770
01:10:03,265 --> 01:10:05,665
I have-- I have no idea.

771
01:10:06,535 --> 01:10:08,400
I don't know.

772
01:10:09,305 --> 01:10:10,795
I'm Hannah.

773
01:10:12,341 --> 01:10:13,899
Hi, Hannah.

774
01:10:14,543 --> 01:10:18,707
I don't know where you got your
information from but it's not correct.

775
01:10:18,881 --> 01:10:21,679
I don't know what you're referring to.

776
01:10:21,850 --> 01:10:25,217
I can't take
any more cases right now...

777
01:10:25,387 --> 01:10:28,447
...but Raymond down the hallway,
perhaps he can.

778
01:10:28,624 --> 01:10:31,354
He can help you
with your civil dispute.

779
01:10:31,727 --> 01:10:33,558
I'm sorry.

780
01:11:32,521 --> 01:11:34,716
Hannah! Hey.

781
01:11:36,859 --> 01:11:38,827
Look, I'm really sorry.

782
01:11:38,994 --> 01:11:39,961
Yeah, she just--

783
01:11:40,329 --> 01:11:41,990
- She didn't even say anything--
- No.

784
01:11:44,566 --> 01:11:47,467
- It wasn't me. I swear.
- What are you, following me now?

785
01:11:47,636 --> 01:11:49,570
- In the car. I'm taking you home.
- No.

786
01:11:49,738 --> 01:11:52,332
I'm not going.
How do you even know where we are?

787
01:11:52,508 --> 01:11:56,308
His girlfriend called me to tell me
and that you had been arrested.

788
01:11:56,478 --> 01:11:57,945
I can't believe you would lie.

789
01:11:58,314 --> 01:12:00,874
- You can't believe I would lie to you?
- In the car.

790
01:12:01,050 --> 01:12:03,678
- We're going home, now. Come on.
- No.

791
01:12:03,852 --> 01:12:06,013
- Get in the car now.
- Fine.

792
01:12:06,388 --> 01:12:07,719
Fine.

793
01:12:09,792 --> 01:12:12,022
- Mr. Lawson.
- Stay out of this, Jason.

794
01:12:12,394 --> 01:12:14,954
- Mr. Lawson, look--
- I said, stay out of it!

795
01:12:15,631 --> 01:12:19,032
- I know how you must feel.
- You have no idea how I must feel...

796
01:12:19,401 --> 01:12:23,497
...and you can't know until you have a
daughter of your own. So stay out of it!

797
01:12:23,972 --> 01:12:26,338
She's not your daughter.

798
01:12:26,942 --> 01:12:30,935
And she has every right
to find out who she is.

799
01:12:35,517 --> 01:12:39,453
I'm gonna make this very simple.
You stay away from my daughter.

800
01:12:39,621 --> 01:12:42,886
You make no contact whatsoever.
Do you understand me?

801
01:12:43,058 --> 01:12:45,026
You lied to me, Jason.

802
01:12:45,394 --> 01:12:47,794
I expected much more from you.

803
01:12:47,963 --> 01:12:49,726
Look at me.

804
01:13:09,051 --> 01:13:11,451
Are we going to talk about this
or what?

805
01:13:15,557 --> 01:13:19,015
Until we get this straightened
I don't think you should go to school.

806
01:13:19,395 --> 01:13:23,661
I see no reason why I should
continue funding this sort of behavior.

807
01:13:24,933 --> 01:13:28,130
- What happened down there anyway?
- Why do you care?

808
01:13:29,471 --> 01:13:33,373
Why do I care? I care
because I'm your father. I love you.

809
01:13:33,542 --> 01:13:36,443
If you love me,
you would have told me.

810
01:13:50,893 --> 01:13:54,556
If you want to know the truth,
I'll tell you. It was three months--

811
01:13:54,730 --> 01:13:57,130
Three months after we adopted you,
we find out...

812
01:13:57,499 --> 01:13:59,899
...the medical bills
are not going to be covered.

813
01:14:00,068 --> 01:14:02,969
We lose the house.
We have to file for bankruptcy.

814
01:14:03,639 --> 01:14:06,665
I am one year, one year away
from finishing med school.

815
01:14:06,842 --> 01:14:09,436
So tell me, how does that
make me the bad guy?

816
01:14:09,611 --> 01:14:11,442
I'm sorry I was such a burden.

817
01:14:12,181 --> 01:14:16,584
- That is not what I said.
- It's what you meant.

818
01:14:17,186 --> 01:14:19,848
Hannah, stop. Stop!

819
01:14:20,889 --> 01:14:23,551
- What was his name?
- What was whose name?

820
01:14:23,892 --> 01:14:25,120
My brother.

821
01:14:29,131 --> 01:14:30,723
I found...

822
01:14:30,899 --> 01:14:32,059
I found my mom.

823
01:14:36,905 --> 01:14:40,068
Sweetheart, I always meant
to tell you about that.

824
01:14:40,909 --> 01:14:42,433
Right.

825
01:14:45,180 --> 01:14:46,875
Jonathan.

826
01:14:49,785 --> 01:14:52,481
Your brother's name was Jonathan.

827
01:15:15,244 --> 01:15:16,643
Hey, guys.

828
01:15:16,812 --> 01:15:20,543
- Oh, look, the prodigal returns.
- Hey.

829
01:15:20,716 --> 01:15:23,480
- Where's Alanna?
- Good to see you too buddy.

830
01:15:24,086 --> 01:15:26,145
You know, if you had been here...

831
01:15:26,522 --> 01:15:28,717
...maybe I wouldn't
have had the audacity...

832
01:15:28,891 --> 01:15:32,759
...to drink something called
a hand grenade.

833
01:15:32,928 --> 01:15:35,897
That would've been a good thing,
because three sips in...

834
01:15:36,064 --> 01:15:38,760
...you don't know
who you are anymore.

835
01:15:40,035 --> 01:15:42,765
When I say I have
no recollection of those events...

836
01:15:42,938 --> 01:15:46,965
...I mean I don't remember anything.

837
01:15:47,643 --> 01:15:49,110
Nothing.

838
01:15:50,879 --> 01:15:54,042
Not the argument, not the fight...

839
01:15:54,216 --> 01:15:56,912
...not this guy, just a little shiner.

840
01:15:59,588 --> 01:16:04,287
Oh, and look, it comes with a court
date, for free, disorderly conduct.

841
01:16:07,663 --> 01:16:11,099
I have a criminal record, Jason.

842
01:16:11,733 --> 01:16:13,792
I'd like to go home.

843
01:16:13,969 --> 01:16:18,030
Oh, I got your luggage,
it's in my room.

844
01:16:18,307 --> 01:16:19,296
Thanks, buddy.

845
01:16:23,679 --> 01:16:25,044
I wanted to say that...

846
01:16:25,948 --> 01:16:28,781
...I went too far and I'm sorry.

847
01:16:33,121 --> 01:16:35,089
- Where are you going?
- Home.

848
01:16:35,257 --> 01:16:37,623
We're going home tomorrow.

849
01:16:46,735 --> 01:16:48,896
I'm going home tonight.

850
01:17:15,197 --> 01:17:17,222
Dr. Lawson, it's Jason.

851
01:17:19,267 --> 01:17:23,260
I wanted to say that I was wrong...

852
01:17:24,773 --> 01:17:28,766
...and I won't be seeing
Hannah anymore.

853
01:17:29,211 --> 01:17:30,940
I'm sorry.

854
01:17:43,959 --> 01:17:47,793
- Hey, can I come in?
- Yeah, sure.

855
01:17:50,666 --> 01:17:52,759
What's all this?

856
01:17:53,068 --> 01:17:54,865
It's financial aid stuff.

857
01:17:56,171 --> 01:18:00,039
Honey, he's not going
to take you out of school.

858
01:18:00,208 --> 01:18:02,267
He's just upset.

859
01:18:05,881 --> 01:18:08,247
I wanna try to explain.

860
01:18:15,123 --> 01:18:16,920
This is you?

861
01:18:17,359 --> 01:18:18,883
Yes.

862
01:18:19,061 --> 01:18:21,962
You look so pretty in this picture.

863
01:18:24,032 --> 01:18:25,932
You look pregnant.

864
01:18:26,101 --> 01:18:30,231
I was. 20 weeks in that picture.

865
01:18:30,405 --> 01:18:31,895
Twins.

866
01:18:32,874 --> 01:18:35,308
You were pregnant with twins?

867
01:18:38,046 --> 01:18:39,741
What happened?

868
01:18:43,085 --> 01:18:44,814
We...

869
01:18:47,022 --> 01:18:48,922
We lost them.

870
01:18:51,326 --> 01:18:55,956
I started volunteering
at this pregnancy crisis center...

871
01:18:58,734 --> 01:19:03,728
...and there was this beautiful
cathedral around the corner...

872
01:19:04,272 --> 01:19:06,763
...and I would go there
to pray at lunch.

873
01:19:07,242 --> 01:19:09,437
And I'll never forget...

874
01:19:10,278 --> 01:19:12,746
...October 17th...

875
01:19:12,914 --> 01:19:14,973
...I went back to work...

876
01:19:15,851 --> 01:19:18,319
...and I saw a bulletin...

877
01:19:19,321 --> 01:19:20,310
...and it said:

878
01:19:20,489 --> 01:19:25,085
"Twins, abandoned...

879
01:19:25,293 --> 01:19:27,818
...twenty-four weeks."

880
01:19:31,099 --> 01:19:33,158
And we knew...

881
01:19:33,502 --> 01:19:37,905
...you and your brother
would have been the same age.

882
01:19:38,774 --> 01:19:43,370
Hannah, you are our miracle.

883
01:19:45,380 --> 01:19:49,009
And that's why it's so hard
to let you go, honey.

884
01:19:51,386 --> 01:19:53,513
You mean so much to us.

885
01:19:54,956 --> 01:19:56,389
I know.

886
01:20:01,163 --> 01:20:03,063
Which cathedral?

887
01:20:04,933 --> 01:20:07,128
It was beautiful.

888
01:21:42,163 --> 01:21:43,187
Excuse me.

889
01:21:45,400 --> 01:21:49,131
I'm sorry,
but we need to close for the evening.

890
01:21:50,171 --> 01:21:54,505
Oh, I didn't know.
I've never been here before.

891
01:21:55,343 --> 01:21:56,901
I'm Hannah.

892
01:21:58,346 --> 01:22:00,041
Hello.

893
01:22:03,385 --> 01:22:06,548
We have services daily,
if you'd like to come back.

894
01:22:07,956 --> 01:22:10,982
I'm actually a-- I'm Baptist.

895
01:22:11,359 --> 01:22:13,384
I guess you should know that.

896
01:22:25,040 --> 01:22:27,099
And why did you come?

897
01:22:28,043 --> 01:22:30,568
I don't know, really.

898
01:22:32,013 --> 01:22:36,643
I guess I'm trying to figure out
how to let go of things.

899
01:22:37,485 --> 01:22:39,419
Things?

900
01:22:40,555 --> 01:22:43,683
I can't figure out how to let go...

901
01:22:44,059 --> 01:22:49,622
...of the fact that I feel hatred
for myself and others.

902
01:22:51,666 --> 01:22:54,191
There, I said it.

903
01:22:55,337 --> 01:22:57,498
What is it that you want to say?

904
01:23:01,009 --> 01:23:02,636
Just say what you feel.

905
01:23:05,580 --> 01:23:09,710
Well, three weeks ago I found out
that my entire life is a lie.

906
01:23:10,418 --> 01:23:13,114
So I went on a trip.

907
01:23:13,688 --> 01:23:17,681
I thought if I went that I would get
all these answers...

908
01:23:18,059 --> 01:23:21,392
...and somehow when I got back
I would feel different.

909
01:23:22,097 --> 01:23:24,088
But I don't.

910
01:23:27,235 --> 01:23:30,568
My parents aren't really my parents.

911
01:23:34,309 --> 01:23:39,303
And my real parents
tried to abort me.

912
01:23:42,150 --> 01:23:44,414
And I have a brother...

913
01:23:44,586 --> 01:23:46,486
Well, I had a brother.

914
01:23:47,055 --> 01:23:50,616
He died shortly after the...

915
01:23:54,129 --> 01:23:57,257
I'm angry at my parents
for not telling me sooner...

916
01:23:57,432 --> 01:24:01,129
...and making me think
that I was just like everybody else.

917
01:24:05,173 --> 01:24:08,301
I'm angry at my real mom...

918
01:24:09,711 --> 01:24:12,202
...for not wanting me.

919
01:24:12,680 --> 01:24:16,446
Why didn't she want me?
What's so wrong with me?

920
01:24:19,687 --> 01:24:21,621
I found her.

921
01:24:24,526 --> 01:24:27,086
And she still doesn't want me.

922
01:24:31,132 --> 01:24:33,123
And I feel guilty.

923
01:24:37,205 --> 01:24:39,332
Part of me feels like...

924
01:24:43,278 --> 01:24:48,113
...he should be alive and I shouldn't.

925
01:24:54,355 --> 01:24:57,483
I wonder if he would have been
a better person than me.

926
01:24:58,726 --> 01:25:01,194
What he would have been like.

927
01:25:04,532 --> 01:25:07,194
It's just l...

928
01:25:07,368 --> 01:25:11,099
I just hate myself
for feeling this way.

929
01:25:15,777 --> 01:25:17,472
I see.

930
01:25:25,587 --> 01:25:28,852
This cathedral...

931
01:25:30,291 --> 01:25:32,521
...was built in 1893...

932
01:25:35,196 --> 01:25:36,857
...named for St. Paul the Apostle.

933
01:25:40,568 --> 01:25:42,502
It's magnificent.

934
01:25:46,341 --> 01:25:50,835
He wrote a letter to the Church
at Colossae and said:

935
01:25:52,347 --> 01:25:55,714
"Because we have been
forgiven by God...

936
01:25:56,618 --> 01:25:59,485
...we should forgive each other."

937
01:26:04,325 --> 01:26:06,259
In Christ you are forgiven...

938
01:26:07,562 --> 01:26:12,829
...and because you are forgiven,
you have the power to forgive.

939
01:26:13,801 --> 01:26:16,531
To choose to forgive.

940
01:26:18,573 --> 01:26:20,404
Let it go.

941
01:26:21,743 --> 01:26:25,543
Hatred is a burden...

942
01:26:26,214 --> 01:26:27,841
...you no longer need to carry.

943
01:26:30,451 --> 01:26:35,354
Only in forgiveness
can you be free, Hannah.

944
01:26:36,591 --> 01:26:42,860
A forgiveness that is well beyond
your grasp or mine.

945
01:26:44,866 --> 01:26:46,697
A forgiveness that...

946
01:26:47,535 --> 01:26:50,265
...you can't find on a trip...

947
01:26:53,308 --> 01:26:55,674
...or even in this cathedral.

948
01:26:59,380 --> 01:27:02,474
But if the Son shall set you free...

949
01:27:03,251 --> 01:27:06,687
...you will be free indeed.

950
01:27:17,632 --> 01:27:21,932
Well, I guess you'd better
close up then, huh?

951
01:27:36,484 --> 01:27:37,883
What was your brother's name?

952
01:27:39,821 --> 01:27:41,982
His name was Jonathan.

953
01:27:43,891 --> 01:27:47,327
Jonathan wants you
to live your life, Hannah.

954
01:27:47,929 --> 01:27:49,897
Live it to the full.

955
01:28:34,442 --> 01:28:35,704
Come in.

956
01:28:43,318 --> 01:28:45,616
I've been giving this
a lot of thought...

957
01:28:46,354 --> 01:28:48,652
...and I wanted to tell you that...

958
01:28:50,858 --> 01:28:51,825
...I am sorry.

959
01:28:53,361 --> 01:28:56,956
I'm sorry that I overreacted.

960
01:28:57,332 --> 01:28:59,630
So you're still enrolled in school.

961
01:29:00,435 --> 01:29:01,561
Thanks, Dad.

962
01:29:02,704 --> 01:29:05,468
And I think
you should probably pack.

963
01:29:05,640 --> 01:29:06,698
What for?

964
01:29:14,582 --> 01:29:15,947
What's this?

965
01:29:19,020 --> 01:29:21,648
I know that you need to finish this...

966
01:29:23,591 --> 01:29:25,058
...but with your permission...

967
01:29:26,794 --> 01:29:28,955
...I'd like to be there when you do.

968
01:29:35,703 --> 01:29:39,730
But there is this one place
I would like to take you...

969
01:29:40,708 --> 01:29:43,802
...on the way, if it's okay with you.

970
01:29:45,546 --> 01:29:47,104
Sure.

971
01:30:15,410 --> 01:30:18,379
The doctor said
there wasn't much brain activity...

972
01:30:20,882 --> 01:30:22,372
...but I saw him smile.

973
01:30:23,785 --> 01:30:26,117
We truly believed
that God would heal him.

974
01:30:27,755 --> 01:30:32,749
We were so young we didn't know what
to tell ourselves so we never told you.

975
01:30:35,496 --> 01:30:38,932
Days became years,
years became decades...

976
01:30:39,100 --> 01:30:41,000
...and you still didn't know.

977
01:30:42,503 --> 01:30:44,471
After he died,
I remember holding you.

978
01:30:44,639 --> 01:30:48,871
I would hold you for hours,
I would not let you out of my sight...

979
01:30:50,144 --> 01:30:54,581
...because I was afraid
that if I lost you too...

980
01:30:57,118 --> 01:31:00,178
So I would just hold you
because I couldn't let go.

981
01:31:02,490 --> 01:31:04,822
And, sweetheart, I still haven't.

982
01:31:05,460 --> 01:31:07,860
And I'm sorry, Hannah.
I'm sorry for the journal.

983
01:31:08,029 --> 01:31:12,193
I'm sorry for keeping so much from
you, for how controlling I've been.

984
01:31:13,067 --> 01:31:15,661
Sweetheart, it's not because
I don't trust you...

985
01:31:15,837 --> 01:31:20,103
...it's because I'm trying honestly
to learn how to trust God again.

986
01:31:21,476 --> 01:31:23,137
So please...

987
01:31:23,945 --> 01:31:25,572
...don't...

988
01:31:26,113 --> 01:31:27,671
Dad.

989
01:31:28,683 --> 01:31:29,980
Yeah?

990
01:31:33,120 --> 01:31:34,644
I...

991
01:31:35,223 --> 01:31:38,920
I love you and it's okay.

992
01:31:42,563 --> 01:31:43,587
Yeah?

993
01:31:50,004 --> 01:31:52,529
Thank you for bringing me here.

994
01:32:20,935 --> 01:32:23,062
You're sure
this is how you want to do it?

995
01:33:32,039 --> 01:33:33,768
Stacey, can...?

996
01:35:12,106 --> 01:35:16,202
- Hello?
- Jason, it's Dr. Lawson.

997
01:35:17,812 --> 01:35:21,179
Yeah, listen, I wanted to say
that I assumed the worst about you...

998
01:35:21,348 --> 01:35:23,782
...but Hannah talked to me.

999
01:35:23,951 --> 01:35:27,045
She told me how you treated her
with respect.

1000
01:35:27,221 --> 01:35:29,416
How much you cared...

1001
01:35:30,725 --> 01:35:32,750
...and I think you should call her.

1002
01:35:33,160 --> 01:35:34,127
I...

1003
01:35:34,295 --> 01:35:37,753
Yeah, listen, I'm not saying
that I think you have to call her...

1004
01:35:37,932 --> 01:35:41,265
...but I just think that you should.
And I'm not trying to pry.

1005
01:35:41,435 --> 01:35:46,737
I just want to know what your
intentions are about my daughter.

1006
01:35:47,842 --> 01:35:49,400
I love her.

1007
01:35:49,944 --> 01:35:52,970
- You need to call her.
- Yeah. Okay.

1008
01:35:53,147 --> 01:35:56,913
- Yeah, I definitely will.
- Thanks.

1009
01:35:59,053 --> 01:36:00,884
- Stupid--
- Hey, baby.

1010
01:36:01,055 --> 01:36:02,488
- Hi.
- Hi.

1011
01:36:16,003 --> 01:36:18,028
Hello?

1012
01:36:19,373 --> 01:36:21,841
What, a date?

1013
01:36:22,309 --> 01:36:23,776
Like, me and you?

1014
01:36:28,983 --> 01:36:31,076
What about my Dad?

1015
01:36:32,319 --> 01:36:35,777
Yeah, I mean, I do. I mean, I will.

1016
01:36:36,791 --> 01:36:38,383
You sure?

1017
01:36:39,326 --> 01:36:40,884
Bye.

1018
01:36:59,280 --> 01:37:01,214
- This is stupid.
- You're stupid.

1019
01:37:01,382 --> 01:37:03,316
- You want to ruin the surprise?
- Yes.

1020
01:37:03,484 --> 01:37:05,281
I dressed for dinner.

1021
01:37:05,452 --> 01:37:07,886
- Five times, actually.
- Five times?

1022
01:37:08,055 --> 01:37:13,823
- I don't go on a lot of dates, obviously.
- Yeah.

1023
01:37:13,994 --> 01:37:15,222
- I'm good.
- Are you good?

1024
01:37:16,297 --> 01:37:19,027
- My dad is scary.
- Yeah, I know that. Okay, ready?

1025
01:37:19,200 --> 01:37:22,465
Three, two, one, open them.

1026
01:37:27,208 --> 01:37:29,039
I thought you should finish.

1027
01:37:29,210 --> 01:37:31,110
- Finish what?
- Your play.

1028
01:37:31,946 --> 01:37:35,109
- What do you think?
- I think we need actors.

1029
01:37:35,983 --> 01:37:38,508
Don't worry,
I was in a play once. Kindergarten.

1030
01:37:38,886 --> 01:37:40,911
- Okay.
- I was Sheep Number 5.

1031
01:37:42,590 --> 01:37:45,991
Hello, Desmond, you can dispense
with the pleasantries...

1032
01:37:46,160 --> 01:37:48,060
...a bit trifle, don't you think?

1033
01:37:49,897 --> 01:37:51,489
I think...

1034
01:37:52,099 --> 01:37:54,363
- They ex-- Have high...
- "Standards for me."

1035
01:37:54,535 --> 01:37:56,298
Standards for me.

1036
01:37:57,171 --> 01:37:58,832
- I'm pretty terrible.
- Yes.

1037
01:37:59,006 --> 01:38:01,440
Yeah. Well, look,
when I was Sheep Number 5...

1038
01:38:01,609 --> 01:38:05,943
...I didn't have lines.
I just-- I wore a sweaty wool suit.

1039
01:38:06,113 --> 01:38:09,241
I did not just say that.
That is ridiculous.

1040
01:38:09,884 --> 01:38:12,910
"l don't suppose
you're talking to family."

1041
01:40:47,641 --> 01:40:50,405
Okay, I think this is the last of it.

1042
01:40:51,545 --> 01:40:53,376
Call us, all right?

1043
01:40:53,547 --> 01:40:57,313
Let us know who your roommate is.
Try not to pick anybody too weird.

1044
01:40:57,484 --> 01:41:00,248
- I'll be fine, Dad, I promise.
- Okay.

1045
01:41:00,421 --> 01:41:02,184
I've got to go.

1046
01:41:04,458 --> 01:41:06,483
- Bye, Dad.
- Bye.

1047
01:41:08,695 --> 01:41:10,492
Mr. Lawson.

1048
01:41:37,791 --> 01:41:39,156
Thank you.

1049
01:41:40,427 --> 01:41:43,624
- For what?
- For wanting me.

1050
01:41:49,203 --> 01:41:50,795
- I gotta go.
- You gotta go.

1051
01:42:09,223 --> 01:42:10,622
I love you, baby.

1052
01:42:44,858 --> 01:42:47,656
Well, initially, Jon called me.

1053
01:42:47,828 --> 01:42:50,228
He said,
"We think that you would play...

1054
01:42:50,397 --> 01:42:52,661
...the birth mother in this film."

1055
01:42:54,168 --> 01:42:55,726
Jon e-mailed me the script...

1056
01:42:55,903 --> 01:42:59,168
...and I was so excited
I think I sat down that very night.

1057
01:42:59,940 --> 01:43:03,569
I got to the point
of the birth mother...

1058
01:43:03,744 --> 01:43:06,804
...and I was so overwhelmed
I started crying over it...

1059
01:43:07,181 --> 01:43:11,208
...because the story actually
had been truly written for me...

1060
01:43:11,385 --> 01:43:15,845
...and Jon and Andy
didn't even know my back-story at all.

1061
01:43:16,857 --> 01:43:17,915
And she read it...

1062
01:43:19,426 --> 01:43:21,223
...and literally called me back...

1063
01:43:21,395 --> 01:43:23,727
...just weeping
about the script and said:

1064
01:43:23,897 --> 01:43:25,364
"How did you know?"

1065
01:43:25,532 --> 01:43:27,659
And we said,
"What are you talking about?"

1066
01:43:27,834 --> 01:43:29,699
And she said:

1067
01:43:30,270 --> 01:43:32,465
"20 years ago
I was working in a law firm."

1068
01:43:32,639 --> 01:43:36,575
Which is very similar to the story.
She said she was in a relationship...

1069
01:43:36,743 --> 01:43:40,543
...she found out she was pregnant
and she decided to have an abortion.

1070
01:43:40,714 --> 01:43:44,309
It was easier to get rid of the child...

1071
01:43:44,484 --> 01:43:46,509
...to not be questioned again...

1072
01:43:46,687 --> 01:43:49,656
...rather than to have a child...

1073
01:43:49,823 --> 01:43:53,725
...and be looked upon at that time
like another failure.

1074
01:44:01,802 --> 01:44:03,599
And...

1075
01:44:05,405 --> 01:44:07,771
So many times...

1076
01:44:09,743 --> 01:44:11,973
...I think
especially as young women...

1077
01:44:12,346 --> 01:44:16,908
...we carry that burden...

1078
01:44:17,284 --> 01:44:20,811
...that we're going to look like a failure.
That it's shameful.

1079
01:44:20,988 --> 01:44:24,446
And, you know,
you can hide a secret...

1080
01:44:24,625 --> 01:44:28,891
...for a long time of abortion
unless you verbally speak about it.

1081
01:44:29,263 --> 01:44:32,699
"Nobody knows. Nobody knows
except my husband, my therapist...

1082
01:44:32,866 --> 01:44:35,630
...and some people like that."
We were blown away.

1083
01:44:35,802 --> 01:44:39,533
Said, "l feel like this is God
telling me it's time for me to share."

1084
01:44:39,706 --> 01:44:44,609
And I remember hearing Jon on the
other line going, "Wow." Like, "Wow."

1085
01:44:44,778 --> 01:44:47,747
From the post-abortive mother, it
was important to be sensitive to that...

1086
01:44:49,383 --> 01:44:51,681
...for this to be
a healing movie for them...

1087
01:44:51,852 --> 01:44:55,811
...and so having Shari's voice
and having her play the role was just...

1088
01:44:55,989 --> 01:45:01,484
...phenomenal to make sure that came
across authentic and very sensitive.

1089
01:45:01,662 --> 01:45:04,256
I think as we went forward...

1090
01:45:04,431 --> 01:45:07,798
...and filmed her scene,
she wasn't acting.

1091
01:45:07,968 --> 01:45:09,731
It was as real as you could get.

1092
01:45:09,903 --> 01:45:13,361
It was one of the more moving things
I've ever seen.

1093
01:45:13,540 --> 01:45:17,271
We went into it
and I remember the cameras rolling...

1094
01:45:17,444 --> 01:45:20,777
...and I just,
right as I walked into the room...

1095
01:45:20,947 --> 01:45:23,313
...I just knew that...

1096
01:45:23,917 --> 01:45:27,318
I just knew
that the Lord was with me.

1097
01:45:28,922 --> 01:45:33,359
And that it was just complete
healing in the moment...

1098
01:45:33,527 --> 01:45:39,659
...that I slide down that door
and that I'm crying and I'm feeling...

1099
01:45:39,833 --> 01:45:43,894
...that wasn't acting,
that was my moment with God...

1100
01:45:44,071 --> 01:45:49,031
...and him with me, to say,
"It's okay, it's over...

1101
01:45:49,543 --> 01:45:51,841
...and you've been forgiven."

